The '''flexible path''' was a set of destinations for further [[human spaceflight|crewed]] [[space exploration]] in the [[inner Solar System]] proposed in the [[Review of United States Human Space Flight Plans Committee]] of 2009 and was envisioned as alternative to the [[Moon]]-first and [[Mars]]-first approaches.{{citation needed|date=March 2014}}<!-- if it was an alternative, then surely we ought to have some sources about these other approaches in US space policy, with links to those particular articles. -->

In 2010 president [[Barack Obama]] announced [[Barack Obama space policy speech at Kennedy Space Center|change in the space policy]] from the Moon-first approach (adopted previously under the [[Vision for Space Exploration]] and [[Constellation program]]) to a variety of destinations resembling{{citation needed|date=March 2014}} the flexible path approach.

== Outer space exploration destinations envisioned in [[Space policy of the United States|US space policy]] ==
'''Bold''' designates missions beyond [[Cis-lunar space]].<br>
<small>'''Legend<blockquote>' &nbsp; [<span style="background-color:lightblue">flyby</span>] — [<span style="background-color:none">orbit</span>] — [<span style="background-color:khaki">landing</span>]</small>

Current as of 2010:{{citation needed|date=March 2014}}
* <span style="background-color:lightblue">[[sub-orbital flight]]s</span>
* [[Low Earth Orbit]] - the [[International Space Station]] ''([[Project Constellation#International Space Station and low-Earth orbit flights|Constellation program]] initial destination'')
''Flexible path'' beyond Low Earth Orbit:{{citation needed|date=March 2014}}
* [[Moon]] <span style="background-color:lightblue">[[Planetary flyby|flyby]]</span> or orbit - for testing and development purposes
* Earth-Moon [[Lagrangian point|L1]] - [[Space rendezvous|assembly]] complex for other missions, servicing of [[propellant depot]]s or other spacecraft such as self-propulsion observatories and reusable non-[[Atmospheric reentry|reentry]] crew or cargo vehicles
* '''Earth-Sun [[Lagrangian point|L2]]''' - servicing of [[Space observatory|space observatories]] requiring Earth shade
* '''Earth-Sun [[Lagrangian point|L1]]''' - servicing of [[Solar observatory|solar observatories]] or manned solar observatory ''([[Apollo Telescope Mount|similar to proposal]] for the [[Apollo Applications Program]])''
* <span style="background-color:khaki">'''[[Near-Earth object]]s'''</span> ''([[Project Constellation#Orion asteroid mission|Constellation program]] third destination'')
* <span style="background-color:lightblue">'''[[Mars]]''' [[Planetary flyby|flyby]]</span>
* <span style="background-color:khaki">[[Moon landing]]</span> ''([[Project Constellation#Lunar sortie/outpost flights|Constellation program]] second destination)''
* '''[[Mars]]''' orbit, including robotic landing and [[sample return]]
* <span style="background-color:khaki">'''[[Mars Moons]]'''</span>
* '''[[Venus]]''' <span style="background-color:lightblue">[[Planetary flyby|flyby]]</span> or orbit<ref name=hsf200910>
[http://www.nasa.gov/pdf/396093main_HSF_Cmte_FinalReport.pdf HSF Final Report:  Seeking a Human Spaceflight Program Worthy of a Great Nation], October 2009, ''Review of U.S. Human Spaceflight Plans Committee'', p. 40.</ref> ''([[Manned Venus Flyby|similar to proposal]] for the [[Apollo Applications Program]])''
* <span style="background-color:khaki">'''[[Mars landing]]'''</span> ''([[Project Constellation#Orion Mars mission|Constellation program]] final destination)''

The list is ordered according to the [[delta-v]] required by the mission.

